{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated function signature matches the expected interface (parameter names, types, return type) specified in the description.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality (signature it chooses from NL spec). A stubbed model can always emit the expected signature and hide real mismatch risk. Rejected Workflow because the behavior text targets one generation outcome (\"generated function signature matches...\") rather than multi-step agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Run a real model generation for several interface-constrained prompts, parse the produced function signature, and assert exact match on parameter names/types and return type against the expected contract.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Orchestration executes attempts in order and returns immediately on the first passing attempt.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module control-flow/state-handoff logic (attempt scheduler + test-result handling), which unit tests of single functions can miss. Rejected System: behavior text does not require real OS/network/subprocess semantics. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: this checks orchestration short-circuiting, not model decision quality.","test_description":"Wire orchestrator, attempt runner, and result evaluator with deterministic stubs: fail attempt 1, pass attempt 2; assert execution order [1,2], no attempt 3 call, and immediate success return from attempt 2.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"For a function that a single call usually fails, the live iterative loop can still produce a passing implementation within the allowed attempts.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"Requires multiple real agentic steps in sequence (generate -> test -> refine -> retest) and depends on real model behavior across attempts. Mocking misses both model adaptation and sequential handoff effects.","test_description":"Use a known prompt where first live generation commonly fails; run full live loop with real model and real test execution, assert a passing implementation is reached within <=3 attempts and record per-attempt outcomes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.69}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When tests fail, the refinement prompt builder includes the failed test names and failure messages in the next LLM prompt.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at module handoff (test runner output -> prompt builder input), not only inside one function. Rejected System: no requirement for real HTTP/subprocess/OS behavior in this behavior itself. Rejected Agentic: assertion is prompt-content construction, not model-output quality.","test_description":"Run test execution producing deterministic failures, pass results through refinement prompt assembly path, and assert the next prompt contains each failed test name and failure message verbatim/structured as expected.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.67,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The next live attempt changes implementation content in response to prior failure context rather than resubmitting the same code.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"This verifies LLM-driven adaptation across sequential stages (prior attempt failure context -> next generation decision). A mock would trivially change or repeat text and hide whether real iterative steering works. Rejected Agentic-only because behavior explicitly depends on cross-step handoff to a subsequent live attempt.","test_description":"Execute live attempt 1 and capture failing feedback; run live attempt 2 with that feedback, then assert attempt-2 code is materially different from attempt-1 code and aligned to the reported failure context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0.65}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The service stops after 3 failed attempts and returns a structured error with all three attempts and their test results.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is orchestration/bookkeeping across modules (retry counter + aggregation + error shaping). Rejected System: behavior text says \"returns a structured error\" but does not require validating a real external HTTP contract or OS/network primitive. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: can be validated with deterministic always-fail stubs; no model-quality dependence.","test_description":"Configure generation/test stubs to fail three times, run orchestrator, assert exactly 3 attempts executed and returned error payload contains attempt 1..3 artifacts and corresponding test results.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full non-agentic pipeline wiring (generate call, test execution, attempt bookkeeping) works end to end with deterministic stubbed model outputs.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"Even with stubbed model outputs, this behavior is end-to-end and includes real test execution; failures can depend on subprocess/filesystem/runtime boundaries that in-process fakes miss. Rejected Agentic/Workflow by explicit text: \"non-agentic\" and \"deterministic stubbed model outputs.\"","t